A sponsor has offered to pay fees for the KCPE student from Budalang&rsquo;i whose father had opted to sell a kidney to raise fees.Erick Onyango, 16, was admitted to Kolanya Boys High School in Busia after scoring 351 in last year&rsquo;s KCPE exam at Sibuka Primary School.Construction company HYoung, whose headquarters is in Nairobi, will pay his fees.Onyango&rsquo;s story was carried in the Star on Tuesday. Speaking to the Star on the phone on Wednesday, HYoung CEO Joseph Swartzman&rsquo;s personal assistant Terry Ogada said the company will meet all of Onyango&rsquo;s expenses.&ldquo;The company has offered to pay fees, buy uniform and other required materials for the student up to university,&rdquo; he said. Onyango&rsquo;s father Felix Juma thanked the company for offering to sponsor his son&rsquo;s education, saying he had lost hope of finding the money. &ldquo;I want to wholeheartedly thank HYoung CEO Swartzman for offering to sponsor my son&rsquo;s education,&rdquo; he said.